## Plan

**Approach:** Add a new internal/replay package whose ResolveInputs(ctx, store, runID, stageName) reads a run ref read-only (Resolve -> ReadFile manifest.json -> runmanifest.ParseJSON), locates the named stage, and returns a structured ResolvedStage: stage metadata (name, git_sha, skill) plus a slice of ResolvedInput, one per recorded ArtifactRef in stage.Inputs. This extracts the read+locate logic that run show (internal/cli/run.go:105-132) already does inline, so later replay beads (phase2.2 worktree, 2.3/2.4 runner) and run show share one resolver with no import cycle (replay imports refstore+runmanifest, both lower-level; neither imports cli).

Scope is resolution only: each ResolvedInput carries {Role, ArtifactRef (the recorded Path/SHA256/Storage/MediaType/Size)} and a ReadContent(ctx) method (or the raw bytes) that reads the blob via store.ReadFile(ctx, ref, artifact.Path). For Storage==content the path resolves to the raw bytes; for Storage==pointer the path is a pointer-record JSON, NOT the external object -- the resolver returns the ref/path and flags it as a pointer (does not attempt to fetch the external object; pointer materialization is a later concern). Materializing inputs to worktree files and feeding a runner are explicitly OUT (phase2.2+).

**Files:**
- internal/replay/resolve.go - NEW. ResolvedStage, ResolvedInput types; ResolveInputs(ctx, store, runID, stageName) function; sentinel errors ErrRunNotFound, ErrStageNotFound, ErrAmbiguousStage. Validates runID via runmanifest.IsValidRunID before any git call.
- internal/replay/resolve_test.go - NEW. Table-driven unit tests (see Tests).
- internal/cli/run.go - OPTIONAL/DEFERRED: note that run show could later call replay.ResolveInputs to avoid duplicated read logic; do NOT refactor in this bead (keep scope tight), just leave the resolver shaped so run show can adopt it later.

**Stage selector semantics (grounded in capture.go append behavior):**
- Select by stage NAME. capture appends stages with no name dedup (capture.go:183), so duplicate names are structurally possible -> if >1 stage matches, return ErrAmbiguousStage naming the stage and count (do not silently pick first/last; replay fidelity demands an explicit choice, which a later bead can add via an index/selector if needed).
- Stage not found -> ErrStageNotFound listing available stage names.
- Run not found -> ErrRunNotFound (map refstore.ErrNotFound); invalid run id rejected before git.
- Read-only: only Resolve + ReadFile; no worktree, no writes (worktree is phase2.2).

**Tests (internal/replay/resolve_test.go, table-driven):** Seed manifests into a t.TempDir() git repo via refstore.WriteCommit (same pattern as run_test.go seedRunWithBadManifest / capture_test.go), NOT the live repo refs (which can change). Cover:
- single-input stage resolves: role+path+storage match, ReadContent returns the exact recorded bytes (verify sha256 of returned bytes == ArtifactRef.SHA256).
- multi-input stage (mirror fixture etude-88o verify stage: two inputs plan+diff) resolves all inputs in recorded order.
- stage-not-found -> ErrStageNotFound, error lists available names.
- duplicate stage name (seed two stages both named plan) -> ErrAmbiguousStage.
- run-not-found -> ErrRunNotFound.
- invalid run id -> rejected before any git call (run in non-repo dir to prove ordering, as run_test.go does).
- pointer input: seed a manifest with a Storage==pointer ArtifactRef; resolver returns the input flagged as pointer and does not error / does not try to fetch the external object.

**Docs:** None needed. Internal resolver with no CLI surface in this bead; the user-facing replay command and any docs land with etude-replay-command. Confirmed no shipped doc references replay input resolution today.

**Risks:** Low. Net-new internal package over an existing, well-tested manifest+refstore model; no new storage format. One judgment call (error on ambiguous duplicate stage names rather than first/last) is the conservative, fidelity-preserving choice and is revisitable when a stage selector/index is added downstream. Tier 1 (reads refs/etude/* namespace) so storage-path/read claims were verified against artifactstore.go + refstore.go, not assumed.

