## Implement (rework after gate BLOCK)

**Context:** Implement gate (attempt 1) was BLOCKed by codex on two non-discriminating tests. Production code in `internal/replay/resolve.go` was confirmed correct by all reviewers; only `resolve_test.go` was changed.

**TestResolveInputsTOCTOU fix:**
The original test advanced the run ref via `runmanifest.Writer.Write` with the SAME bytes at `inputRef.Path`, so a buggy ref-reading impl (`ReadFile(ref, path)` instead of `ReadCommitFile(commit, path)`) would still return the original bytes and the test would vacuously pass.

Fixed by: advancing the ref via `store.WriteCommit` DIRECTLY (bypassing runmanifest.Writer hash validation) with DIFFERENT bytes (`"toctou-input-OVERWRITTEN-by-concurrent-capture"`) at the same `inputRef.Path`. Added assertions that `result.Commit != newCommit` (snapshot pinned to original) and that `ReadContent` returns the ORIGINAL bytes. A ref-reading impl would now read the overwritten bytes and fail the content equality check.

**TestResolveInputsReadContentPropagatesError fix:**
The original test hand-built a `ResolvedInput` struct with a manually-copied closure and called that closure — never touching the production `ReadContent` returned by `ResolveInputs`. A broken production closure would still have let the test pass.

Fixed by: seeding the run via `store.WriteCommit` directly (omitting `inputRef.Path` from the commit tree — bypassing runmanifest.Writer which rejects missing artifact files), then calling `ResolveInputs` (which reads only manifest.json and succeeds), then calling the PRODUCTION `result.ResolvedInputs[0].ReadContent(ctx)` closure, which hits `ReadCommitFile` and returns `refstore.ErrNotFound`. Removed all hand-built closure code.

Also removed now-unused `"fmt"` import.

